|| Baconytics
=====================

Get a local copy of the Baconytics repository with this command:
	git clone git@github.com:aliuy/Baconytics 
	
If you have Eclipse and the Google Plugin for Eclipse installed already, just import the project into eclipse.

Installing Eclipse and the Google Plugin for Eclipse
====================================================
Download Eclipse if you don't have it:
    http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/

The plugin includes everything you need to build, test and deploy your app, entirely within Eclipse.
The plugin is available for Eclipse versions 3.3, 3.4, 3.5, 3.6, 3.7.
You can install the plugin using the Software Update feature of Eclipse.

The installation locations are as follows:
    The Google Plugin for Eclipse, for Eclipse 3.3 (Europa):
        http://dl.google.com/eclipse/plugin/3.3
    The Google Plugin for Eclipse, for Eclipse 3.4 (Ganymede):
        http://dl.google.com/eclipse/plugin/3.4
    The Google Plugin for Eclipse, for Eclipse 3.5 (Galileo):
        http://dl.google.com/eclipse/plugin/3.5
    The Google Plugin for Eclipse, for Eclipse 3.6 (Helios):
        http://dl.google.com/eclipse/plugin/3.6
    The Google Plugin for Eclipse, for Eclipse 3.7 (Indigo):
        http://dl.google.com/eclipse/plugin/3.7

If you need more help, see: http://code.google.com/appengine/docs/java/tools/eclipse.html

Running the Application
=======================
Once you have your Eclipse workspace set up, run the project as a Google Web Application.

You can view the application through your browser at http://localhost:8888/

To run the scraper, direct your browser to http://localhost:8888/scraper

You can view the datastore through the admin console at http://localhost:8888/_ah/admin
